## Risks

Medium: schema extension of a currently‑permissive `constructorElement`
`$def` (schema `:201`) while preserving the nine reserved anchors
(Project.fs:42) and keeping `saveProject`/`openProject` round‑trip green —
mis‑numbering or renaming an anchor breaks every existing project fixture.
Modelling R3 non‑orthogonality (A.4.4) correctly so AC‑A4 holds is the
main numerical care‑point; reuse the engine `Angle` type to avoid a parallel
rotation representation.

## Hand-off

State‑of‑the‑world for this slice must carry the new baseline counts in a
fenced `gates:` YAML block keyed by `berreman_unit_tests` (legacy suite) and
the constructor‑test count, so downstream `count_at_least` gates have a
baseline. Record the `ElementPlacement` / `BoundingBox` / `CatalogueKind`
shapes and the emission smart constructor's public surface so slice 002
(RayModel) and slice 004 (Table/Drawer) can consume them. Note that
`Project.fs` and the project schema still need their **table** extension
(slice 004) — leave the placement anchors stable for that follow‑on edit.
